{% comment %}
  Features Section - Groovy World Homepage
  Shows the 3 main reasons/benefits (Screenshot-Vorlage)
{% endcomment %}

<div id="reasons" class="features-section" style="background: #f0f8fd; padding: 80px 20px;">
  <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <!-- Badge -->
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 18px;">
      <span style="display: inline-block; font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; color: #ff6b35; border: 2px solid #ff6b35; border-radius: 20px; padding: 4px 18px; letter-spacing: 1px; background: #fff; font-weight: 600;">REASONS</span>
    </div>
    <!-- Section Title -->
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 18px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 3.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #2d5da1; margin: 0 0 10px 0; line-height: 1.1;">Why Should I Use<br>Groovy?</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 60px;">
      <p style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.15rem; color: #666; margin: 0; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
        Our approach sets us apart from traditional tracing books.<br>Here's why Groovy is the ideal choice.
      </p>
    </div>
    <!-- Features Grid -->
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr)); gap: 40px;">
      <!-- Feature 1: Tactile Feedback You Can Feel -->
      <div style="background: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 32px; text-align: center; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10); transition: transform 0.3s ease;">
        <div style="width: 80px; height: 80px; margin: 0 auto 20px auto; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
          <img src="{{ 'guidance-4.svg' | asset_url }}" alt="Tactile Feedback You Can Feel" style="width: 64px; height: 64px;" />
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin: 0 0 15px 0;">Tactile Feedback You Can Feel​</h3>
        <p style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; font-weight: 400;">
          Our dotted grooves don't just show the way—they let children feel each letter or number as they trace it, whether with their finger or pencil.​<br>
          That gentle resistance gives instant feedback when they're on the right path, helping them develop muscle memory and spatial awareness.​<br>
          It's more than tracing—it feels like they've really written something.​
        </p>
      </div>
      <!-- Feature 2: Engaging Visuals, Frustration-Free Practice -->
      <div style="background: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 32px; text-align: center; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10); transition: transform 0.3s ease;">
        <div style="width: 80px; height: 80px; margin: 0 auto 20px auto; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
          <img src="{{ 'fun-1.svg' | asset_url }}" alt="Engaging Visuals, Frustration-Free Practice" style="width: 64px; height: 64px;" />
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin: 0 0 15px 0;">Engaging Visuals, Frustration-Free Practice​</h3>
        <p style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; font-weight: 400;">
          Groovy Books combine bold, kid-friendly visuals with clear step-by-step guidance—ideal for visual learners.​<br>
          No clutter, no confusion—just fun, focused pages that reduce frustration and turn practice into a positive, rewarding experience.​
        </p>
      </div>
      <!-- Feature 3: Not Just How to Write—But How to Write Beautifully -->
      <div style="background: white; padding: 40px; border-radius: 32px; text-align: center; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.10); transition: transform 0.3s ease;">
        <div style="width: 80px; height: 80px; margin: 0 auto 20px auto; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
          <img src="{{ 'writing-1.svg' | asset_url }}" alt="Not Just How to Write—But How to Write Beautifully" style="width: 64px; height: 64px;" />
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 700; color: #111; margin: 0 0 15px 0;">Not Just How to Write—But How to Write Beautifully​</h3>
        <p style="font-family: 'Preahvihear', sans-serif; font-size: 1.05rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; font-weight: 400;">
          Groovy doesn't just teach the mechanics of writing.​<br>
          By guiding every stroke and reinforcing it through tactile and visual memory, children gradually develop neat, consistent, and beautiful handwriting—with time, confidence, and joy.​
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

